beer_description: Seek and ye shall find! Luscious apricot and peach aromas are delicately interwoven with spicy suggestions of nutmeg and cinnamon in this heavenly soft, golden treasure.

Just in time for the holidays is our special treat. A dark and chewy bock beer. Around November you'll find 'chocolate bock' on tap down at the brewery.
No other beer has a more pure and intense malt character as a true Bock. Many large breweries in the U.S. have diluted the original strength of this beer, but we make the real thing. The body of this beer is rich, making it a good beer to warm up to during those "special" Iowa winters. The blackened malt that we use in it gives the brew a slight hint of chocolate. Its a smooth brew, having been lagered for over a month in our cellars, in true bock style.

This is the ideal beer to make a cold and chilly winter evening cozy.
The ingredients are: seven types of malt (including rolled oats), two types of Belgian hops, brewing water and yeast.
Our winter beer is a dark and heartwarming beer with a full pure, slightly sweet taste and long soft bittery aftertaste.

Yes, there really is pumpkin in this beer, along with cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and ginger to give this beer a mild pumpkin pie finish. Don?t worry, all of these ingredients are filtered out before it?s kegged.
A full-bodied, dark brown ale with a complex malt aroma and flavor due to the chocolate, caramel and black malts. One of the best English style ales found in the new world.
A "true" German style weizen, unfiltered, complete with citrus, clove, banana and vanilla flavors produced naturally by the wheat and a special yeast strain.
Brilliant deep color, medium-bodied and modestly hopped. Produced from five malts and four different hops, it?s the perfect balance for many beer lovers.
A sweet, malty, medium-bodied lager, lightly hopped and golden in color. Aged slowly to produce a smooth clean taste. A great beer for any time or day.
Eisbock (Ice Bock) was inadvertently invented by Kulmbacher after a barrel was left out in the brewery yard in the dead of winter. Ice crystals are removed, concentrating the flavor.

Pours copper with a small off white head, quickly dissipated. Aroma is caramel, hay, cereal and nutty. Taste is sweet with toasted bitters, mostly sweet. Medium bodied, average carbonation, somewhat sticky.

Redhook?s second recipe ever brewed, remains a gold standard for porters. A Northwest revival of the traditional London-style porter, Blackhook?s roasted malts, hop bitterness and velvety texture make it a favorite of dark beer fans everywhere.
A smooth, full-bodied nut brown ale, lightly hopped with a hint of roasted chocolate and crystal malts.  This ale is dark in color without the heavy taste of porter or stout.
Alluring and intriguing, a legendary doppelbock with malt complexities hinting at dark fruit and mysterious sugars. Brandy Snifter time!

beer_description: This Maibock pours a rustic yellow with aromas of semi sweet malts, grainy and underlying noble hops.

Liefmans Goudenband is one of the most distinctive dark beers in the world. Originally called IJzerenband (Iron Band) ? a reference to the iron bands around the beer barrels ? the bottle gained its champagne cork when it was renamed Liefmans Goudenband (Gold Band). Made in open vats with beer of mixed fermentation, it is left to mature for four to 12 months in the cellar. Mature beer is then fortified with younger beer, so the fermentation process starts up again.

Liefmans Goudenband is a beer for storing, and just keeps improving over the years like a fine wine. Even after ten years, this dark red beer tastes as fresh as ever. You?ll immediately pick up on the wonderful aromas of caramel, apple, rhubarb, cherries and malt. On the taste buds you will find hints of apple and cherries, combined with woody notes, while the aftertaste hints at nuts and dried raisins. The mildly acidic taste make this beer a perfect match for blue cheese.
A classic American style pale ale which is light golden in color, slightly malty and smooth. generous dry hopping contributes to the it?s aromatic character and dry, balanced finish.

Tyskie is a pattern Gronie taste lager in the world. Perfectly composed flavor profile provides a strong bitterness and malt fully, while satisfying the desire.

Tyskie is made from carefully selected ingredients: malted barley, hops and water, using natural yeast in the beer fermentation.

Perfectly given Tyskie Gronie attracts the attention of a thick white foam, clarity, and light golden color.

Seasoned drinker senses in the notes of malt, delicate aroma of hops, and even touches of apple and banana. Gronie years gaining recognition in Poland and in the world. As the only Polish beer, twice won the "Beer Oscars" - Grand Prix at The British Brewing Industry Awards, the most prestigious beer competition in the world.

Edison Light is brewed with only water, hops, yeast and 100% malted barley--no adjuncts, enzymes or dextrose found in other light beers. Edison Light has a fresh hop aroma and unexpected flavor derived from a proprietary (patented formula) along with undertones of spicy floral and citrus notes.

beer_name: James Squire Australian Best Ale Limited Release

beer_description: Traditionally brewed to celebrate the harvest season, this reddish-brown lager has a rich caramel character and a long flavorful finish. Its delicious malty sweetness is nicely accented by a slightly fruity bouquet and a mild hop flavor.

A beer that truly started Samuel Adam's odyssey into extreme brewing. Its deep, full flavor explodes with notes of maple, vanilla, oak and toffee. This flavor, along with the rich mouth feel, has drawn comparisons to a vintage port, sherry, and cognac; and Samuel Adams Triple Bock should be enjoyed in much the same way. We recommend serving it at room temperature in a snifter a few ounces at a time - one bottle should generously serve two to three.  Its warming malt character and fruit esters make it an ideal after dinner aperitif.

There have been only three vintages produced: 1994, 1995 and 1997. 1994 and 1995 vintages are marked as such on the back label; 1997 vintage is not.
Full-bodied Oktoberfest Ale with robust malt and hop signature. Rich, toasty flavor, finishes mellow with a note of hoppiness.

A Festbier, not a M?rzen.
A full rich bodied, hoppy, seasonal lager. Especially brewed for the Festbier season. This beer truly represents the Bavarian way of celebrating. Deep gold color, great mouthfeel and lots of flavor. Prost!

This ale has a nice clean taste with a dry finish. Hallertau and Chinook hops blended with Harrington and victory malts make this a very enjoyable ale. W.C. derives its name from well known fruit grower, from Michigan?s western coast,by the name of William Capen. This ale is great companion with a hand full of fresh cashews.

Full Tilt?s assertive aroma and flavor are derived from the generous use of fresh hops, which are added during the brewing and fermentation. The five different specialty malts give it depth of flavor and a surprising mouthfeel.

Harvey?s Brewery Christmas Ale is a strong dark barley wine is reminiscent of the strong ?stock ales? drunk during the eighteenth and nineteenth centuries and should be treated with respect.

To help celebrate the December festive season, draught Christmas Ale will be available whilst stocks last, as part of the Harvey?s Brewery range of ?Seasonal Ales?.
This strong golden ale is marked by passion fruit and herbal notes in the aroma, with suggestions of banana and honey in the complex palate. The Tripel has a remarkably long and smooth finish.

Created in the mid-nineties, Riggwelter is our flagship Strong ale. We wanted a beer with real strength and depth so we developed a unique recipe built around rich espresso aromas, dark fruit and roasted malt flavours which lends itself perfectly to putting in a bottle.

beer_description: 6 types of malt & 4 hearty hops additions

This traditional style German Wheat beer (pronounced) Hah-fuh-vite-zen) remains unfiltered to preserve it's natural smooth flavor and aroma. Don't be alarmed by its cloudy appearance or noticeable sediment. The slight banana and clove aroma comes from the authentic German Hefeweizen yeast. It has a light refreshing finish.

Chief BlackHawk Porter is a robust black and sharply bittersweet ale. This style was traditionally the session beer consumed by the porters in London.

Hold your glass to the light and you may glimpse dashes of garnet dancing through this dark, black ale. Count on a dense and creamy mocha head to rise a few inches and leave a sticky, lacy trail down the sides of your glass as it slowly settles.

The aroma of coffee beans and bittersweet chocolate will water your mouth. Visions of sticking your finger in a bowl of thick, fudgey batter or stealing a darkened and decadent 
chocolate chip cookie might creep into your thoughts. A variety of dark, roasted malts?Brown, Chocolate, Black?lend rich flavors and deep colors to this ale.

beer_description: Gulpener Dort is Nederlands eerste speciaalbier, voor het eerst gebrouwen in 1953. Dort is een variant op de Duitse Dortmunder. Hou je van echt karaktervol bier, dan drink je Gulpener Dort. Een heerlijk amberkleurig authentiek Limburgs bier met een gracieuze, volmoutige en licht zoete smaak. Dort kan goed gecombineerd worden met hartige en pittige maaltijden, chili gerechten, hamburgers en barbecue.

beer_description: Don?t be fooled by this name! Milkhouse Stout is not a sweet stout, as its name seems to imply. This is a dry stout with a rich roasted flavor and an ample dose of hops. We use a blend of five different barleys to achieve the robust taste that will tantalize your taste buds with every sip. Best served at about 45F in a room temperature pint glass.

A local favorite, this ale gets its distinctive hoppy nose from a generous portion of Chinook hops. A blend of Harrington, Munich, Vienna, barleys give this beer a full clean taste that is truly refreshing. This ale mates well with a fine cigar and a warm summer night in the backyard that is your kingdom.

This ale is an American Style Wheat. The smooth taste of this golden ale is derived from a simple grain bill of harrington barley. Shawano Gold is an excellent choice for thoses touges that prefer a lighter taste. But be adviced that this ale is far from being like a typical american lager, it still carries the full flavor that makes Slab City Beers the local choice in premium malt beverages.

beer_description: Brown in color with ruby and garnet highlights, this strong Scotch Ale is sweet and earthy on the nose. Rich flavors of caramel malt and bready notes, this beer exhibits light fruity esters, reminiscent of dates and dark stone fruits, along with the light smoky-earthy characters the style is known for. Ales in Scotland were traditionally named for their strength, and relative cost, in shillings. This beer would be understated as a 120 Shilling Ale.
Malty, rich, firm head & lacing.

A rich and robust blend of light, caramel, and dark malts sets the stage for BBC Dark Star Porter?s robust presence on the palate. This smooth but robust porter has complex notes of chocolate and roasted grains balanced by additions of traditional English hops, creating a delicious chocolaty and smooth ale.

An American standard, BBC APA is a full bodied and heavily hopped American Ale. It is copper in color and brewed with a blend of pale and crystal malts, balancing the citrus and pine flavors from large doses of American and English hops to create a very drinkable, hoppy ale. BBC APA is a hophead?s dream!
An Imperial India Pale Ale with an intense citrus hop aroma, a huge malt body and a crisp finish.
Traditional Bavarian Hefeweizen

This brew is a past winner of the Silver Medal at the Great American Beer Festival.  It is a deep golden, medium-bodied lager which gets its color, body & sweet malt character from imported Vienna malt.

A smooth, well-balanced ale brewed with pure water, malts, hops, and yeast and then cold conditioned in the tradition of a classic German Altbier. The drinkable nature of this beer and the roasted chocolate and coffee notes present in this beer make it a wonderfully warming beer. A subtle malt sweetness, distinctive German hops aroma and taste, and subtle roasted finish make this one of our favorite styles of beer.
Whitetail Cream Ale is a easy drinking session ale. Gold, with a light to medium body. Whitetail's flavor is delicately hop balanced for a clean, crisp finish.

This Dubbel style Belgian beer is created in the great Belgian tradition. Pale Malt, Caramel and Special B Malts impart a unique sweetness to this beer. The traditional Belgian yeast fully ferments the Belgian Candi Sugar to give a satisfying taste that is twice what a Belgian pale delivers.

Since 1860, Schell?s Bock meant spring was around the corner. And until recently, tradition and climate dictated the seasonality of Bock beers. Today, with the ability to control strict brewing environments, we?re able to usher in a new tradition?August Schell Caramel Bock, available year-round. 
This medium-bodied, dark copper beer sports a light caramel flavor with a hint of malt sweetness. We figured beer drinkers aren?t seasonal, so why should beer be?

This American Pale Ale is our flagship brand, celebrating hop bitterness and aroma.  Dry-hopping with three different varieties in the fermenter gives our Paddy it's signature hop-forward bite and rich "nose''.
